HEADWORD: Quassation
<hw>Quas*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>quassatio</ets>, from <ets>quassare</ets> to shake. See
<er>Quash</er> to crush.]</ety> <def>The act of shaking, or the state of
being shaken.</def> <rj><au>Gayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

